From: joe@apache.dtcc.edu (Joe Brown)
Subject: Q: Serial port Control; need TD signal on so CallerID box will work
Date: 18 Sep 1993 16:54:35 -0400

Hi netters,

Has anyone managed to get the CLASSMATE model 10 to work?

This is a caller ID device, grabbs power from three lines of serial
port.

  TD (Transmit Data)          - the tricky one
  CTS (Clear to Send)         - both of these are on, when simply
  DTR (Data Terminal Ready)     by reading the serial line.
                                ie.  cat /dev/ttyS0

I can't figure out how to turn on the Transmit Data (TD) line, and 
still read characters.  It looks like ioctl isn't implemented in
the kernel, which I assume, the calls to perform this action, would
exist.

I've looked at setserial, and there's no explicit opitions for doing
this.  It may be necessary to hack at the code, which looks like the
most viable option, to me, at this point.

Any thoughts, aspirations, questions/answers?

Well, at least I've found a use for my 286, for now... :-)
